President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring November 9, 2014, as World Freedom Day. This day commemorates the tearing down of the Berlin Wall 25 years ago and honors the courage and determination of those who fought for freedom. The proclamation highlights the importance of solidarity and sacrifice in the pursuit of peace and human dignity. It also emphasizes the responsibility of every nation to uphold peace and security. The proclamation calls upon the people of the United States to observe this day with appropriate ceremonies and activities, reaffirming their dedication to freedom and democracy.